# Spring Retry & Spring Cache

## Spring Retry

### When to Retry
- Transient failures only: network timeouts, temporary unavailability, optimistic lock exceptions
- **NEVER** retry non-idempotent operations without an idempotency key
- **NEVER** retry business validation failures or permanent errors (4xx)

### Declarative (`@Retryable`)
```java
@Service
public class PaymentGatewayService {

    @Retryable(
        retryFor = {ConnectException.class, SocketTimeoutException.class},
        noRetryFor = {BusinessValidationException.class},
        maxAttempts = 3,
        backoff = @Backoff(delay = 1000, multiplier = 2.0, maxDelay = 10000)
    )
    public PaymentResult processPayment(PaymentRequest request) {
        return gateway.charge(request);
    }

    @Recover
    public PaymentResult recoverPayment(ConnectException ex, PaymentRequest request) {
        log.error("Payment gateway unreachable after retries for order {}", request.orderId(), ex);
        return PaymentResult.queued(request.orderId());
    }
}
```

### Programmatic (`RetryTemplate`)
Use when retry logic is complex or conditional:
```java
@Bean
public RetryTemplate retryTemplate() {
    return RetryTemplate.builder()
        .maxAttempts(3)
        .exponentialBackoff(1000, 2.0, 10000)
        .retryOn(ConnectException.class)
        .build();
}
```

### Retry vs Circuit Breaker
| Concern | Spring Retry | Resilience4j Circuit Breaker |
|---------|-------------|------------------------------|
| Scope | Single operation | Aggregated failure tracking |
| Use when | Transient failure, few retries | Dependency repeatedly failing |
| Combines with | Circuit breaker wraps retry | Retry inside circuit breaker |

### Configuration
```java
@Configuration
@EnableRetry
public class RetryConfig { }
```

## Spring Cache

### Annotations
| Annotation | Purpose |
|-----------|---------|
| `@Cacheable` | Cache the return value; skip execution on cache hit |
| `@CacheEvict` | Remove entry from cache |
| `@CachePut` | Always execute and update cache |
| `@Caching` | Combine multiple cache operations |
| `@CacheConfig` | Class-level defaults (cache name, key generator) |

### Cache Key Design
- Use explicit `key` SpEL expressions for clarity
- Never rely on default key generation for methods with multiple parameters
- Include all parameters that affect the result
```java
@Cacheable(value = "products", key = "#category + '-' + #page")
public Page<Product> findByCategory(String category, int page) { }

@CacheEvict(value = "products", allEntries = true)
public void updateProduct(Product product) { }
```

### Backend Selection
| Backend | Use Case |
|---------|----------|
| `ConcurrentMapCacheManager` | Local, single-instance, dev/test |
| Redis (`RedisCacheManager`) | Distributed, multi-instance production |
| Caffeine (`CaffeineCacheManager`) | Local, high-performance, size/time eviction |

### TTL and Eviction
- Always set TTL; unbounded caches cause memory leaks
- Configure per-cache TTL with `RedisCacheConfiguration`:
```java
@Bean
public RedisCacheManager cacheManager(RedisConnectionFactory factory) {
    var defaultConfig = RedisCacheConfiguration.defaultCacheConfig()
        .entryTtl(Duration.ofMinutes(30))
        .serializeValuesWith(SerializationPair.fromSerializer(new GenericJackson2JsonRedisSerializer()));

    var cacheConfigs = Map.of(
        "products", RedisCacheConfiguration.defaultCacheConfig().entryTtl(Duration.ofHours(1)),
        "sessions", RedisCacheConfiguration.defaultCacheConfig().entryTtl(Duration.ofMinutes(15))
    );

    return RedisCacheManager.builder(factory)
        .cacheDefaults(defaultConfig)
        .withInitialCacheConfigurations(cacheConfigs)
        .build();
}
```

### Anti-Patterns
- Caching mutable objects without defensive copy
- Caching null values without explicit `unless` condition
- Missing `@CacheEvict` when data changes
- Caching inside the same class (proxy self-invocation bypass)
- No TTL leading to stale data or memory exhaustion

### Configuration
```java
@Configuration
@EnableCaching
public class CacheConfig { }
```

## Testing
- Use `ConcurrentMapCacheManager` in tests (no Redis dependency)
- Verify cache hits: call method twice, assert downstream called once
- Verify eviction: update, then verify next read fetches fresh data
